The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Gangjee, Ghei in fray

 A STAFF REPORTER

Calcutta: Rahil Gangjee, Harmeet Kahlon, Gaurav Ghei and Amandeep Johl will be in fray at the inaugural $400,000 Amby Valley Asian Masters to be held at the Amby Valley City Golf course, from May 11 to 14. 

According to information received here, a strong international field will feature as many as 20 winners on the Asian PGA Tour. Also in fray will be home talents like Vijay Kumar, Firoz Ali, Ali Sher and Mukesh Kumar. 

Australian powerhouse Terry Pilkadaris, a three-time Asian Tour winner who has been ranked inside the top-five of the Order of Merit for the past two seasons, will lead the challenge. He has won a title in every season since his double victory in China in 2004. 




